defaultWritten defaultevidence submitted by defaultThe Wildlife Trustsdefault default&#xa0;defaultThere are 37 individual Wildlife Trusts in England.  They are actively engaged in the planning system, promoting opportunities to improve the natural environment and reviewing more than 70,000 planning applications last year.  The Wildlife Trusts have more than 740,000 members in England including members of our junior branch Wildlife Watch.
