defaultStrategic ldefaultocation of offsetsdefault6.1
default&#xa0; 
defaultFor offsetting to be reasonable, there must be a meaningful ecological and social relationship between the development site and the compensatory scheme. This should be as close to the development as possible, ideally within the same district or county, but at the very least within the same sub regional level. 
defaultThe Wildlife Trusts 
defaultdo not accept 
defaultthat offsetting should be evenly distributed across the country - where development pressures are lower, the requirement for offsets will also be lower.
