defaultIdentification of land for biodiversity offsetting would enable the quantum of habitat required to be assessed at a strategic level, taking into account: direct habitat loss; and the in-
defaultcombination and indirect pressures. It would also ensure that the offset is in a geographical area that will enable 
defaultcolonisation
default by populations displaced by development
